Spring boot is a module of spring framework which is used to create stand-alone, production-grade Spring based Applications with minimum programmerâ€™s efforts.


https://start.spring.io use this URL for Spring Initializer.
Add required dependencies. Project will be created. 
In pom.xml lookup for parent directory, which looks like this.
<parent>
		<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
		<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
		<version>2.2.2.RELEASE</version>
		<relativePath/> <!-- lookup parent from repository -->
</parent>
Create a controller with a @RestController annotation. Create a method with @RequestMapping which maps the http request to handler methods.
Run the spring boot application.
In url type localhost:8082, port no. can be changed in application.properties file by simply writing server.port=8082.
